	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I was wondering if somebody here has some info on mapper 221. I found a cartridge inside one of my famiclones and dumped the rom. Here's the cartridge:
<br /><a href="http://jpx72.detailne.sk/modd_files/fc/front.jpg" class="postlink">http://jpx72.detailne.sk/modd_files/fc/front.jpg</a>
<br /><a href="http://jpx72.detailne.sk/modd_files/fc/back.jpg" class="postlink">http://jpx72.detailne.sk/modd_files/fc/back.jpg</a>
<br />Then I found a simillar rom "700-in-1" (google 700-in-1 [p1][U][!] ), converted header to iNes and found it's #221. So I added this header to my dump and it worked. I also sent this dump to a member here and it somehow ended on the internet (google 1000-in-1 (JPx72) [!] ). 
<br /><img src="http://jpx72.detailne.sk/modd_files/fc/snaps/700-in-1/title.gif" alt="Image" />
<br />This cartridge means a lot to me, and I will like to have a backup copy of it, even if it means to create exact copy and reproduce the whole logic:
<br />74LS32
<br />74LS161
<br />74LS32
<br />74LS153
<br />74LS273
<br />74HC04
<br />74LS08
<br />28 pin RAM chip
<br />27C080 (exact pinout, no need to rewire).
<br />But I was wondering if the cartridge cannot be reproduced on some other mapper, something simple...

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


