		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />A game generally can't be moved to a simpler mapper. This is especially the case with multicarts which are designed to maintain compatibility with discrete mappers in order to not need to mapper hack every game. Common mappers do NOT have the ability to emulate simple discrete mappers like this, so you have no choice but to reproduce the mapper in discrete chips or in programmable logic. If you had a NROM multicart where games didn't bankswitch, that would be a different story, though you'd still have to modify common mappers to be able to address 8M of PRG ROM.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


